<h1>MICROBIOLOGY </h1>
<font face="monospace" size="5">
Microbiology is the study of microorganisms, which are organisms that are too small to see without a microscope. Microorganisms are essential to life on Earth. <br><br>

<b>What does microbiology study? </b>
<i><b>Viruses:</i></b> How viruses function inside cells<br><br>

<i><b>Bacteria:</i></b> How bacteria cause disease<br><br>

<i><b>Fungi:</i></b> How fungi cause disease, such as ringworm and athlete's foot<br><br>

<i><b>Parasites:</i></b> How parasites cause disease<br><br>

<i><b>Algae:</i></b> How algae contribute to life on Earth<br><br>

<i><b>Protozoa:</i></b> How protozoa cause disease, such as amoebic dysentery and malaria<br><br>

<b>Subdisciplines of microbiology: </b><br>
bacteriology, mycology, phycology, parasitology, virology, protistology, and immunology.<br><br>


