<h3>SUBDISCIPLINES OF MICROBIOLOGY</h3>

<section id="boxes">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="box">
          <img src="protistology.jpg">
          <h4>PROTISTOLOGY</h4>
          <p>Protistology is the scientific study of protists, which are a diverse group of organisms that are not animals, plants, or fungi. Protists are important in food webs and can be pathogens.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="box">
          <img src="virology.jpg">
          <h4>VIROLOGY</h4>
          <p>Virology is the scientific study of viruses, including their structure, evolution, and the diseases they cause. It's a subfield of microbiology and pathology.Â  </p>
        </div>
        <div class="box">
          <img src="bacteriology.jpg">
          <h4>BACTERIOLOGY</h4>
          <p>Bacteriology is the study of bacteria and archaea, which are single-celled organisms that are vital to life on Earth. Bacteriology is a branch of microbiology that also includes the study of the genetics, biochemistry, and ecology of bacteria.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
